Volodymyr Zelensky, the Ukrainian President, spoke at a news conference with EU officials after a summit in Kyiv. He stated that Ukraine will defend their eastern city, Bakhmut, and requested that the West provide them with long-range weapons to help Kyiv drive out Russian forces from the Donbas region. He said: "Ukraine would be able to hold Bakhmut and liberate occupied Donbas if it received long-range weapons." PLEASE FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...